      "content": "Hey, I'm looking over the draft for the Q3 quarterly call. The User Acquisition Cost (CAC) numbers are looking pretty bad this quarter—way higher than we projected. If we lead with these numbers, I'm worried the shareholders are gonna panic and we'll see a massive sell-off. How should we handle the CAC increase in the presentation to keep everyone calm and maintain confidence in NexaTech?",
